parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Rear Subframe and Differential Mounting Point Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear subframe and differential mounting point can cause the rear axle assembly to become loose, leading to erratic handling and making the vehicle unsafe to drive, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Loud clunking sound coming from the rear end
rear differential mounting point separated from the body of the vehicle
spot weld failure
trunk floor pan spot welds breaking loose
rear axle assembly loose
erratic handling.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear differential mount can cause the rear end of the vehicle to hang, leading to loss of control and potential accidents, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: The rear differential mount bracket splits or breaks
causing the rear end to sag or hang
abnormal noises or vibrations from the rear of the vehicle
difficulty handling or loss of control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The defective seat rails can cause the driver and passenger seats to move back and forth during stops, especially downhill, creating a safety hazard for the driver and an uncomfortable situation for the passenger. This can lead to a loss of control while driving, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The driver and passenger seats move back and forth during stops
especially downhill
the seats shift unexpectedly while accelerating or braking
the seats do not remain in a fixed position.
